<TITLE> Joint forces widen search for abducted Danida staffers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bandarban, June 26 (bdnews24.com)  An armed gang demanded Tk 40 lakh in ransom for freedom of two Danida staffers abducted in Bandarban Monday. Joint forces Tuesday widened an operation to trace Hossain Shahid Sumon and his driver Mohammad Hanif, who are believed to be kept in a dense forest. A gang of 12 abducted the staffers of Danish International Development Agency from Khiburipara of the district. Several security sources said the demand for ransom was made from an unknown place. None of the sources disclosed the identity of the ransom seekers. A rescue team, led by additional police super Mosharaf Hossain Miazi, visited the scene where the two were abducted. BDR officers detained one Keuburi Marma from Kaburi area Tuesday morning. He was interrogated. Deputy commissioner Abdul Majid Shah Akhand, district police super Abdul Kader and senior military officers held a meeting Tuesday at Bandarban cantonment. Witnesses say the members of the gang were carrying AK-47s. They searched for a foreign Danida official. And then they rowed away with a trawler with the Danida staffers on board. bdnews24.com
